Vol / Page: 1/59
Edition:
Quote:  ... nay, he may with due deference to public opinion, carry (<i>pekau</i>) pickback, the said foreigner, be his dimensions long or short, ... <i>Ibid.</i> 1/171-172 The flax in a basket generally weighs about from [172] eighty to a hundred pounds, and is either carried (<i>pikou</i>), on men's shoulders or in canoes, to the house of the purchaser.
